properties.name: cs_specversion__c
properties.description: The version of the schema, correlated to specversion.

properties.name: ce_id__c
properties.description: An identifier specific to this event.  ce_source+ce_id must be unique.  Correlates to id.

properties.name: ce_source__c
properties.description: URI-reference.  Identifies the context or application/service where the event occurred.  Correlates to source.

properties.name: ce_type__c
properties.description: Describes the type of event related to the originating occurrence.  Correlates to type.

properties.name: ce_time__c
properties.description: Represents when the event occurred.  RFC 3339 compliance timestamp with UTC offset.

properties.name: content_type__c
properties.description: Usually "application/json", but values per RFC 2016 and its modifications.  Correlates to datacontenttype.

properties.name: correlation_id__c
properties.description: An identifier assigned by the ce_source or ingestion point which should persist through the entire downstream cascade so we can tie them all together.

properties.name: boMilitaryService__c
properties.description: When true, indicates that the individual is self-reporting as having served, or is currently serving in the US Armed Forces. Includes enlisted persons that may not have served in ‘Active Duty’ status, and service in the National Guard or Reserves. Also includes ‘surviving spouses’ of Veterans who served and were Missing In Action (MIA) /Killed In Action (KIA), who died of a condition or impairment connected to their service in the Armed Forces (as determined by VA or DoD), or who self-report that their spouse’s service and connected disability/impairment entitles them to benefits from the VA.  URLA form field 7a.1

properties.description: A value from a MISMO prescribed list that specifies duty status of current or former military personnel.  URLA form field 7a.2

properties.name: boSurvivingSpouse__c
properties.description: When true, indicates that the individual is a surviving spouse of a Veteran who served and was Missing In Action (MIA) /Killed In Action (KIA), a Veteran who died of a condition or impairment connected to his/her service in the Armed Forces (as determined by VA or DoD), or a Veteran whose service connected disability/impairment, they believe, entitles them to benefits from the VA.  URLA form field 7a.2.1

The total dollar amount of assets associated with an account. Collected in the Total field for Section 2a on the URLA.  URLA form field 2a.5

Despite being a yes/no question on the URLA, the value used in the ULAD is either "Manufactured" or (null).  The question asked on the form is "Is the property a manufactured home? (e.g., a factory built dwelling built on a permanent chassis)".
